# FinWise AI - Claude Rules

## Project Context

This project is FinWise AI, an AI-powered Financial Intelligence Platform developed for the SmartBridge Vibe Coding Internship.

The application must satisfy internship requirements while maintaining production-quality architecture suitable for a professional portfolio.

---

## Always Follow

- Follow DESIGN.md for UI and visual language.
- Follow .ai/project_rules.md for engineering standards.
- Build only the requested module.
- Never modify unrelated files.
- Never change architecture without approval.

---

## Tech Stack

Framework: Astro

Language: TypeScript

Styling: Tailwind CSS v4

Icons: Lucide

AI: Groq (llama-3.3-70b-versatile)

Database: Google Sheets

Deployment: Vercel

---

## Coding Rules

- Write modular code.
- Prefer reusable components.
- Keep components small.
- Separate business logic from UI.
- Never use inline CSS.
- Avoid duplicate code.
- Use strict TypeScript.
- Handle loading and error states.

---

## Financial Rules

Loan eligibility, EMI calculations, and financial formulas must be implemented locally.

AI is used only for reasoning, explanations, and recommendations.

---

## Workflow

When asked to build a feature:

1. Understand the request.
2. Create reusable components.
3. Keep files organized.
4. Wait for review before starting the next module.

Never build the entire application unless explicitly instructed.
